---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { site } from '../../data/site';
import { personJsonLd } from '../../data/schema';
import { compliance } from '../../data/compliance';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Why Laura Bohanon Chose Davidson Homes — New Construction in Owens Cross Roads and Hampton Cove, AL"
  description="Laura Bohanon joined Davidson Homes because Davidson is a semi-custom production builder — more options and upgrades than a standard production build. Her primary community is Ramsay Cove in Owens Cross Roads, Alabama."
  schema={[personJsonLd]}
  canonicalPath="/why-davidson/"
>
  <section class="section-alt" style="padding-top:4rem">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:800px">
      <h1 class="section-title">Why Laura Chose Davidson Homes</h1>

      <p style="font-size:1.1rem;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:2rem;line-height:1.6">
        Laura has worked with buyers across builders and markets over 18 years. She did not end up at Davidson by accident.
      </p>

      <p>
        In January 2023, after nearly two decades in residential real estate across northern Alabama,
        Laura made a deliberate decision to focus exclusively on new construction. She had options.
        She chose Davidson Homes.
      </p>

      <p>
        The reason was straightforward: Davidson is a semi-custom production builder. That matters.
        Most production builders work from a fixed set of floor plans with limited finish options.
        Davidson gives buyers more — structural options, upgrade choices, elevation selections —
        across each home series. You are not just choosing countertops. You can influence how the
        home is actually built, within the series. That level of flexibility is rare at the
        production price point.
      </p>

      <p>
        That is not marketing language. It is what Laura observed after walking buyers through
        the process and comparing it to what she had seen at other builders. Davidson's
        construction quality and semi-custom model stand up — and they are why she is
        comfortable putting her name next to theirs.
      </p>

      <h2 style="margin:2.5rem 0 1rem">Ramsay Cove, Owens Cross Roads</h2>

      <p>
        The majority of Laura's work right now is in Ramsay Cove, a Davidson Homes community
        in Owens Cross Roads, Alabama. Ramsay Cove is in Madison County, on Highway 431,
        about 19 miles from Huntsville. It is in the New Hope school district.
      </p>

      <p>
        Laura knows the lots, the floor plan series available in the community, the upgrade
        options at each tier, and the current build cadence. She can tell you what to ask
        before you sign and what to watch for during the build process.
      </p>

      <h2 style="margin:2.5rem 0 1rem">Hampton Cove and Madison County</h2>

      <p>
        Davidson also builds in Hampton Cove and other Madison County communities.
        If you are exploring communities outside Ramsay Cove, Laura can speak to
        what Davidson builds across the area, not just one community.
      </p>

      <h2 style="margin:2.5rem 0 1rem">A note on representation</h2>

      <p>
        Laura is a licensed agent at Davidson Homes LLC. Her role is as a sales agent
        for Davidson communities. In Alabama, representation is established through a
        written agreement. The right conversation to have is before you tour, not after
        you sign.
      </p>

      <div class="compliance-notice">
        This is the personal website of Laura Bohanon and is not operated by or endorsed by Davidson Homes LLC. {compliance.recadNotice}
      </div>

      <div style="margin-top:2.5rem">
        <a href="https://www.davidsonhomes.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-outline" style="margin-right:1rem">View Davidson Homes Communities</a>
        <a href={site.phoneHref} class="btn btn-primary">Call Laura: {site.phoneDisplay}</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
